ZH: 我今天早上吃了一碗豆浆。
EN: I had a bowl of soy milk this morning.

ZH: 她拿了一碗米饭。
EN: She took a bowl of rice.

ZH: 他一口气喝完了一碗牛肉面。
EN: He finished a bowl of beef noodles in one go.

ZH: 昨天晚上我碗里的面条很辣。
EN: The noodles in my bowl were very spicy last night.

ZH: 你可以给我递一碗汤吗？
EN: Can you pass me a bowl of soup?

ZH: 她端着一碗水果冰淇淋走了过来。
EN: She walked over with a bowl of fruit ice cream.

ZH: 我碗里的水不够了。
EN: My bowl is running out of water.

ZH: 你今天早饭吃了一碗粥吗？
EN: Did you have a bowl of porridge for breakfast today?

ZH: 奶奶总是给我准备一碗热汤。
EN: Grandma always prepares a bowl of hot soup for me.

ZH: 这个碗是中国的传统陶瓷。
EN: This bowl is traditional Chinese ceramics.

ZH: 她的碗摔成碎片了。
EN: Her bowl broke into pieces.

ZH: 那家餐馆的碗都是手工制作的。
EN: The bowls at that restaurant are all handcrafted.

ZH: 他把碗放在碗架上。
EN: He put the bowl on the rack.

ZH: 我抓住碗的边缘。
EN: I grabbed the edge of the bowl.

ZH: 爷爷喝完了一碗鸡汤。
EN: Grandpa finished a bowl of chicken soup.

ZH: 那个碗很容易打破。
EN: That bowl is very easy to break.

ZH: 我今天早上没有时间吃一碗粥。
EN: I didn't have time to eat a bowl of porridge this morning.

ZH: 我爱在冬天吃一碗热腾腾的鸡汤。
EN: I love having a bowl of steaming hot chicken soup in winter.

ZH: 这个碗有一个漂亮的图案。
EN: This bowl has a beautiful pattern on it.

ZH: 她在碗里盛了一勺糖。
EN: She scooped a spoonful of sugar into the bowl.
